new_moon.interpretation: Born during the New Moon, you operate primarily through instinct and impulse. Your approach to life is spontaneous and subjective—you act first and analyze later. This phase indicates a personality that initiates without needing external validation. Your challenge is developing objectivity and learning from others' perspectives. You're here to start new cycles, trusting your gut even when you can't explain your knowing. The seed of consciousness is planted but not yet emerged into full awareness.

crescent_moon.interpretation: Born during the Crescent Moon, you're a natural fighter who breaks from the past to establish new directions. Your life involves struggle against inherited patterns or limitations. This phase indicates determination to become something different from your origins. Your challenge is knowing when to stop fighting and accept support. You're here to pioneer new possibilities by courageously separating from tradition. The sprout breaks through soil—visible but vulnerable.

first_quarter.keywords: crisis in action, decision, building, manifestation
first_quarter.interpretation: Born during the First Quarter Moon, you face crises of action that force decisive choice. Your life involves building structures and manifesting intentions through concrete action. This phase indicates a personality that must act despite obstacles. Your challenge is overcoming doubt and commitment fears. You're here to translate vision into reality through persistent effort. The plant grows visibly—commitment to form is unavoidable.

gibbous_moon.interpretation: Born during the Gibbous Moon, you analyze, refine, and perfect what you've built. Your life involves dedication to improvement and preparation. This phase indicates a personality focused on doing things right. Your challenge is accepting good enough and not getting lost in endless refinement. You're here to develop skills and prepare for meaningful contribution. The bud forms—not yet flowering but pregnant with potential.

full_moon.interpretation: Born during the Full Moon, you seek fulfillment through relationship and objective understanding. Your life involves balancing opposing forces and seeing multiple perspectives. This phase indicates a personality that needs others to complete themselves. Your challenge is maintaining identity while deeply engaging with otherness. You're here to illuminate through clarity and achieve wholeness through integration of opposites. The flower blooms—maximum visibility and vulnerability.

disseminating_moon.interpretation: Born during the Disseminating Moon, you share what you've learned and teach through demonstration. Your life involves communicating meaningful understanding to others. This phase indicates a personality with something important to share. Your challenge is accepting that not everyone wants what you offer. You're here to spread seeds of wisdom that may bloom in future generations. The flower forms seeds—giving away accumulated knowledge.

last_quarter.keywords: crisis in consciousness, reorientation, transformation, wisdom
last_quarter.interpretation: Born during the Last Quarter Moon, you face crises of consciousness that force reorientation. Your life involves questioning established systems and transforming understanding. This phase indicates a personality that must break down old structures. Your challenge is not becoming bitter or cynical about necessary destruction. You're here to facilitate transition and prepare ground for new growth. The plant dies back—composting for future fertility.

balsamic_moon.interpretation: Born during the Balsamic Moon, you release the past and prepare for future emergence. Your life involves endings, transitions, and prophetic vision. This phase indicates a personality that sees what's coming before it arrives. Your challenge is functioning in the present while perceiving future potentials. You're here to midwife transition and hold space for what's dying and what's being born. The seed forms in darkness—pregnant with next cycle's potential.

solar_return.interpretation: Your Solar Return chart—calculated for the moment the Sun returns to its exact natal position—reveals the themes and opportunities of your upcoming year. This annual 'birthday chart' shows what the universe is emphasizing in your life from one birthday to the next. Pay special attention to which houses are activated and any planets closely aspecting your natal placements.

progressions.interpretation: Secondary Progressions reveal your psychological and spiritual age, which may differ from your physical age. Each day after birth equals one year of internal development. Your progressed chart shows how you've matured internally and what developmental themes are currently active in your psyche.

chiron.description: Chiron represents your deepest wound and your greatest healing gift. Where you've been most hurt is precisely where you develop the capacity to heal others. This asteroid shows both your vulnerability and your wisdom.

chiron_in_sign.Aries: Your wound involves identity, assertion, and the right to exist. You may have experienced invalidation of your selfhood or been told your needs don't matter. Your healing gift is teaching others to courageously be themselves and honor their anger and autonomy.
chiron_in_sign.Taurus: Your wound involves worth, security, and the physical body. You may have experienced material instability or shame about your body/needs. Your healing gift is teaching others to value themselves and find security through self-worth rather than external validation.
chiron_in_sign.Gemini: Your wound involves communication, intelligence, and being heard. You may have been silenced, mocked for your ideas, or told you're not smart enough. Your healing gift is teaching others to trust their voice and that all perspectives have value.
chiron_in_sign.Cancer: Your wound involves nurturing, family, and emotional safety. You may have lacked adequate care or been made responsible for others' feelings too young. Your healing gift is teaching others healthy emotional boundaries and that it's okay to need care.
chiron_in_sign.Leo: Your wound involves creativity, visibility, and special-ness. You may have been shamed for standing out or told your creative expression was worthless. Your healing gift is teaching others that everyone deserves to shine and be celebrated.
chiron_in_sign.Virgo: Your wound involves perfection, usefulness, and health. You may have internalized that you're only valuable if perfect or experienced chronic health issues. Your healing gift is teaching others that wholeness includes imperfection and that being is as important as doing.
chiron_in_sign.Libra: Your wound involves relationships, fairness, and belonging. You may have experienced rejection, betrayal, or been forced to choose sides. Your healing gift is teaching others that harmony doesn't require self-abandonment and that conflict can be creative.
chiron_in_sign.Scorpio: Your wound involves power, trust, and intimacy. You may have experienced betrayal, abuse, or violation of boundaries. Your healing gift is teaching others that vulnerability is strength and that transformation is possible after trauma.
chiron_in_sign.Sagittarius: Your wound involves meaning, truth, and belonging to something larger. You may have been shamed for your beliefs or experienced spiritual abuse. Your healing gift is teaching others that meaning is personal and that questioning is sacred.
chiron_in_sign.Capricorn: Your wound involves authority, achievement, and maturity. You may have been forced to grow up too fast or had harsh, critical authority figures. Your healing gift is teaching others that worthiness isn't earned through achievement and that discipline can be compassionate.
chiron_in_sign.Aquarius: Your wound involves belonging, authenticity, and difference. You may have been ostracized for being different or forced to conform. Your healing gift is teaching others that uniqueness is a gift and that true belonging comes from being authentic.
chiron_in_sign.Pisces: Your wound involves boundaries, spirituality, and reality. You may have been overwhelmed by others' emotions or experienced spiritual bypassing. Your healing gift is teaching others that compassion includes self-compassion and that groundedness enables transcendence.

fixed_stars.description: Fixed stars are distant suns whose influence has been observed for millennia. When a fixed star conjuncts (within 1°) a natal planet or angle, it adds a specific flavor or destiny quality to that point. These are ancient influences predating the zodiac.

Algol.keywords: the demon star, transformation through crisis, facing the shadow
Algol.interpretation: Algol, the most feared star in traditional astrology, conjuncts this point. You carry the archetype of Medusa—the one who transforms rage and trauma into power. This placement often indicates experiencing something 'evil' or traumatic that forces you to confront darkness. Your gift is the ability to face what others deny, transmute poison into medicine, and ultimately protect others from what harmed you. The Medusa energy turns those who gaze upon her to stone—you may freeze or be frozen by trauma, but ultimately develop the power to shield others.

Pleiades.keywords: the weeping sisters, ambition through sorrow, heightened sensitivity
Pleiades.interpretation: The Pleiades, known as the Seven Sisters, conjunct this point. You carry extraordinary sensitivity and ambition born from sorrow. Traditional astrology associated this with 'something in the eyes'—both literal vision issues and the ability to 'see' what others miss. You may experience losses that drive achievement or success that feels bittersweet. Your gift is transforming grief into creative accomplishment and understanding that ambition can be motivated by love for what's been lost.

Aldebaran.keywords: the watcher of the east, integrity, honor, success through right action
Aldebaran.interpretation: Aldebaran, one of the four Royal Stars, conjuncts this point. You're held to high standards of integrity—success comes through honorable action, but falls away if you compromise ethics. This star brings achievements but demands you remain true to your principles. Your gift is the ability to lead with honor and the understanding that true success is built on integrity rather than expedience.

Rigel.keywords: the foot of Orion, teaching, invention, lasting achievement
Rigel.interpretation: Rigel, the bright foot star of Orion the Hunter, conjuncts this point. You have gifts for teaching, invention, and creating lasting knowledge. This star indicates the ability to take bold action and achieve recognition, often in educational, technical, or leadership fields. Your gift is bringing light through knowledge and the courage to pursue ambitious goals.

Betelgeuse.keywords: the shoulder of Orion, honor, riches, lasting success
Betelgeuse.interpretation: Betelgeuse, the great red giant star on Orion's shoulder, conjuncts this point. This star brings honors, success, and material prosperity, often in military, martial, or leadership contexts. You have the capacity for lasting achievement and the ability to inspire others through courage and action.

Sirius.keywords: the dog star, the brightest star, ambition, fame, the divine
Sirius.interpretation: Sirius, the brightest star in the sky, conjuncts this point. You carry powerful ambition and potential for fame or recognition. Ancient cultures considered Sirius sacred—you may have a sense of divine purpose or destiny. This star indicates leadership abilities and the capacity to 'shine' brightly. Your challenge is managing the intensity of this energy without burning out or becoming arrogant. Your gift is the ability to inspire others and achieve significant recognition.

Regulus.keywords: the heart of the lion, kingship, success through generosity, the fall through revenge
Regulus.interpretation: Regulus, the Royal Star and Heart of the Lion, conjuncts this point. You have natural leadership abilities and potential for significant success and recognition. Traditional astrology warns that Regulus's gifts fall away if you seek revenge—success comes through magnanimity and generosity, not vengeance. Your gift is the ability to lead with heart and inspire loyalty. Your challenge is maintaining nobility of character when wronged.

Spica.keywords: the wheat sheaf, gifts, protection, artistic success
Spica.interpretation: Spica, the star of the Virgin's wheat sheaf, conjuncts this point. This is considered one of the most fortunate stars, bringing gifts, protection, and success, particularly in artistic or Venusian fields. You have natural talents that attract opportunity and a protective quality that helps you avoid the worst consequences of mistakes. Your gift is the ability to create beauty and attract positive circumstances.

Arcturus.keywords: the bear guardian, honor, riches, navigation
Arcturus.interpretation: Arcturus, one of the brightest stars and ancient navigation aid, conjuncts this point. You have the ability to guide others and find your way through complexity. Success comes through honorable action and the ability to see the bigger picture. Your gift is helping others navigate their paths while maintaining your own direction.

Antares.keywords: the heart of the scorpion, the rival of Mars, obsession, daring
Antares.interpretation: Antares, the Heart of the Scorpion and Rival of Mars, conjuncts this point. This star brings intensity, daring, and sometimes recklessness. You have tremendous drive and the willingness to risk everything for what you believe in. Traditional astrology associates this with 'troubles with eyesight'—both literal and metaphorical blindness to consequences when passionately pursuing goals. Your gift is the courage to go where others fear and the ability to transform through intensity.

Fomalhaut.keywords: the watcher of the south, idealism, the fall from grace, fame
Fomalhaut.interpretation: Fomalhaut, one of the four Royal Stars, conjuncts this point. This star brings idealism and potential for recognition, but traditional astrology warns of 'sudden fall from high position' if ethics are compromised. You're called to maintain high ideals and spiritual integrity. Success through this star is real but conditional on remaining true to principles. Your gift is the ability to inspire through idealism when you embody your values.

void_of_course_moon.description: The Moon is Void of Course (VOC) when it has made its last major aspect in its current sign before changing to the next sign. Traditional astrology considers this 'dead time' when actions taken tend not to manifest as expected. Plans made, purchases, contracts, and new beginnings during VOC Moon often come to nothing or require redoing.
void_of_course_moon.advice: During VOC Moon, focus on routine tasks, meditation, creative work, and going with the flow rather than initiating important matters. Wait for the Moon to enter the next sign before signing contracts, starting projects, making major purchases, or scheduling important meetings.

sabian_symbols.description: Each of the 360 degrees of the zodiac has a unique Sabian Symbol - a poetic image channeled by clairvoyant Elsie Wheeler in 1925. These symbols provide specific, oracular insight into the exact degree placement of your planets.

1.symbol: A woman just risen from the sea; a seal is embracing her
1.interpretation: Emergence from the unconscious into conscious existence. The birth of new identity through embracing one's instinctual nature. You come into being through contact with primordial forces.

2.interpretation: The ability to see and reflect the absurdities of existence with humor. You understand that laughter reveals truth more effectively than seriousness. Your gift is showing others themselves through playful observation.

3.symbol: A cameo profile of a man in the outline of his country
3.interpretation: Individual identity merged with collective destiny. You embody cultural or ancestral qualities that define you. Your personal story reflects a larger narrative beyond yourself.

4.symbol: Two lovers strolling through a secluded walk
4.interpretation: Private intimacy away from the world's demands. The need for sacred space where relationship can develop without external interference. You value creating protected environments for connection.

5.interpretation: Mental concepts taking flight. Abstract ideas becoming mobile and communicable. You have the ability to elevate thought beyond limitation and share visionary thinking.

6.symbol: A square brightly lit on one side
6.interpretation: Illumination revealing only partial truth. Understanding that all perspectives are limited by their vantage point. You learn to accept incomplete knowledge while acting with available light.

7.symbol: A man successfully expressing himself in two realms at once
7.interpretation: The ability to bridge different worlds simultaneously. You function effectively in multiple contexts, translating between them. Mastery comes through integration rather than choosing one path.

8.symbol: A large hat with streamers flying, facing east
8.interpretation: Readiness to greet new experience with openness and celebration. Your identity expands through welcoming what comes from the horizon. Ceremonial preparation for transformation.

9.interpretation: The ability to perceive potential futures and hidden patterns. You see through surface appearances into underlying structure. Prophetic vision that reads signs others miss.

10.symbol: A teacher gives new symbolic forms to traditional images
10.interpretation: Education through revelation rather than tradition. You bring forth what wasn't previously known. Your teaching comes from direct insight into emerging patterns.

11.interpretation: Authority earned through representing collective will. Leadership that embodies what the group needs expressed. You carry responsibility for articulating shared purpose.

12.symbol: A triangularly shaped flight of wild geese
12.interpretation: Instinctual organization for collective migration. Natural hierarchies that serve survival and progress. You understand how to move with others while maintaining formation.

13.interpretation: Potential destruction that doesn't manifest. Crisis averted through grace or timing. You learn that not all threats actualize—sometimes things simply don't go off.

14.symbol: A serpent coiling near a man and a woman
14.interpretation: Temptation or wisdom entering relationship. The introduction of knowledge that changes innocence. You face choices about whether to remain naive or embrace complexity.

15.interpretation: Patient craftsmanship creating warmth and protection. Traditional skills producing practical beauty. You understand that meaningful work requires sustained attention and cultural continuity.

16.symbol: Brownies dancing in the setting sun
16.interpretation: Hidden helpers celebrating the completion of daily work. Magic that appears at thresholds between day and night. You recognize support from unseen forces during transitions.

17.symbol: Two prim spinsters sitting together in silence
17.interpretation: Dignified restraint and unspoken understanding. Communication beyond words in relationships that honor boundaries. You value proper form and meaningful silence.

18.symbol: An empty hammock stretched between two trees
18.interpretation: Rest awaiting occupancy. Potential for relaxation that goes unused. You learn about readiness without forcing—the invitation to ease when you're prepared to accept it.

19.symbol: The magic carpet of Oriental imagery
19.interpretation: Transportation through imagination rather than physical means. Fantasy as legitimate vehicle for change. You travel through visualization and creative thinking.

20.symbol: A young girl feeding birds in winter
20.interpretation: Compassion for vulnerable life during harsh conditions. Nurturing what cannot fend for itself. You maintain caring through difficulty, sustaining what would otherwise perish.

21.interpretation: Willingness to engage in direct combat for what matters. Courage to step into the arena and fight. You don't shy from confrontation when principles are at stake.

22.symbol: The gate to the garden of all fulfilled desires
22.interpretation: Standing at the threshold of manifestation. Access to abundance requires only entry. You learn that fulfillment awaits on the other side of taking action.

23.symbol: A woman in pastel colors carrying a heavy and valuable but veiled load
23.interpretation: Grace under the weight of responsibility. Valuable obligations that strain but don't break you. You carry what's precious despite difficulty, though others may not see the burden.

24.symbol: Blown inward by the wind, the curtains of an open window take the shape of a cornucopia
24.interpretation: Abundance entering through openness to external forces. Allowing life to fill you rather than grasping. You receive plenty when you create receptive space.

25.symbol: A double promise reveals its inner and outer meanings
25.interpretation: Commitments operating on multiple levels simultaneously. Understanding that agreements have both literal and symbolic dimensions. You honor both surface and depth meanings.

26.symbol: A man possessed of more gifts than he can hold
26.interpretation: Overwhelming abundance requiring selectivity. More blessings than can be utilized. You learn that having everything means choosing what to actually use.

27.symbol: Lost opportunity regained in the imagination
27.interpretation: Redeeming what was missed through creative revisioning. The second chance that exists in mental realms. You transform regret into renewed possibility through reimagining.

28.interpretation: Collective expectations not met. The experience of failing to deliver what was anticipated. You learn about disappointment as teacher and the courage to face unfulfilled hopes.

29.interpretation: Cosmic harmony underlying existence. The mathematical perfection of celestial movement. You attune to universal order and the music inherent in structure.

30.symbol: A duck pond and its brood
30.interpretation: Nurturing provided through natural environment. Safe waters for young life to develop. You create or find protected spaces for growth and family development.

31.interpretation: Pure flow from elevated sources. Clarity and freshness that originates in high places and brings refreshment. You channel pristine energy from peak experiences.

32.interpretation: Sudden discharge of accumulated tension. Natural forces demonstrating power dramatically. You experience breakthrough through intensity that clears the atmosphere.

33.symbol: Steps up to a lawn blooming with clover
33.interpretation: Effort leading to simple abundance. Natural prosperity awaiting those who make the climb. You find that elevation brings you to fields of good fortune.

34.interpretation: Treasure at the meeting of earth and heaven. Reward found where different realms intersect. You discover value through bridging material and spiritual.

35.symbol: A widow at an open grave
35.interpretation: Facing loss with dignity. Standing at the threshold between life and death with what remains. You learn strength through grief and the reality of endings.

36.symbol: A bridge being built across a gorge
36.interpretation: Creating connection across dangerous divisions. Engineering relationship between separated places. You build passages over what seems unbridgeable.

37.symbol: A woman of Samaria at the ancestral well
37.interpretation: Drawing from traditional sources despite being outsider. Access to spiritual nourishment across social boundaries. You find sustenance in heritage that isn't originally yours.

38.symbol: A sleigh on land uncovered by snow
38.interpretation: Inappropriate tools for current conditions. Resources designed for different circumstances. You adapt when what worked before no longer fits the situation.

39.interpretation: Celebration adorning natural life. Culture embellishing what grows freely. You bring festivity and meaning through ornamentation of the simple.

40.interpretation: Service during crisis with training and compassion. Organized aid during suffering. You provide skilled help when others face their darkest hours.

41.symbol: A woman watering flowers in a garden
41.interpretation: Nurturing beauty through patient attention. Cultivation of what blooms. You maintain loveliness through consistent care and devotion to growth.

42.interpretation: Dreaming together of future acquisition. Shared fantasy about material life without yet possessing. You build relationship through imagining what you'll create together.

43.interpretation: Bearing others' burdens for compensation. Service through strength and endurance. You carry weight that isn't yours as part of your work.

44.interpretation: Instinctual exploration and innocent joy in tidal zones. Different modes of engagement with liminal spaces. You balance primitive seeking with playful discovery.

45.symbol: A man muffled up, with a rakish silk hat
45.interpretation: Contradiction between protection and display. Covering vulnerability while asserting personality. You navigate between hiding and showing yourself.

46.symbol: An old teacher fails to interest his pupils in traditional knowledge
46.interpretation: Wisdom losing relevance to new generations. The challenge of transmitting what no longer resonates. You face the obsolescence of cherished understandings.

47.symbol: A battle between the swords and the torches
47.interpretation: Conflict between force and enlightenment. Physical power versus illuminating truth. You witness or participate in struggles about how to create change.

48.symbol: A woman airing an old bag through a sunny window
48.interpretation: Exposure of accumulated dust to purifying light. Cleansing what's been stored in darkness. You refresh what's been kept too long without air.

49.interpretation: Fresh ground emerging from primordial waters. New territory for exploration and settlement. You encounter virgin possibilities requiring pioneering.

50.symbol: Wisps of winglike clouds streaming across the sky
50.interpretation: Ethereal movement suggesting transcendence. Beauty in transition and the temporary. You appreciate fleeting grace and changing forms.

51.symbol: A finger pointing to a line in an open book
51.interpretation: Specific guidance within accumulated wisdom. Being directed to exact knowledge needed. You find precise answers when you consult traditional sources.

52.symbol: A white dove flying over troubled waters
52.interpretation: Peace descending on chaos. Hope appearing during crisis. You recognize or embody the messenger of resolution during turbulence.

53.symbol: A jewelry shop filled with magnificent gems
53.interpretation: Concentrated beauty and value on display. Abundance of precious objects offered for acquisition. You encounter overwhelming wealth of treasures to choose from.

54.symbol: A mounted Indian with scalp locks
54.interpretation: Warrior carrying trophies of conquest. Pride in victories over enemies. You display what you've won through combat and skill.

asteroids.description: Beyond the major planets, thousands of asteroids add nuanced detail to your chart. The major asteroids represent archetypal energies, while personal name asteroids create intimate cosmic signatures.

1.name: Ceres
1.keywords: nurturing, motherhood, food, agriculture, loss and return
1.interpretation: Ceres shows how you nurture and wish to be nurtured. Where you care for others, your relationship with food and resources, and how you handle separation. This is the Great Mother asteroid - your capacity to feed, sustain, and let go.

in_signs.Aries: You nurture through encouragement to be independent. Feeding others' courage and initiative. May struggle with smothering vs. freedom.
in_signs.Taurus: You nurture through physical comfort and material security. Food and touch are your love languages. Natural at creating abundance.
in_signs.Gemini: You nurture through communication and mental stimulation. Teaching and conversation feed your soul. May over-think care-giving.
in_signs.Cancer: You nurture instinctively and emotionally. Food equals love. Deeply maternal/paternal regardless of gender. Can be clingy.
in_signs.Leo: You nurture through celebrating others. Generous praise and attention. Need appreciation for your care-giving.
in_signs.Virgo: You nurture through service and health consciousness. Practical care and problem-solving. Can be critical in attempts to help.
in_signs.Libra: You nurture through creating harmony and beauty. Relationship-focused care. May avoid necessary confrontation.
in_signs.Scorpio: You nurture through intense emotional bonding. Transformative care that goes deep. Can be possessive.
in_signs.Sagittarius: You nurture through sharing wisdom and adventure. Freedom within care. May neglect daily practical needs.
in_signs.Capricorn: You nurture through structure and responsibility. Serious about care-giving. May be emotionally reserved.
in_signs.Aquarius: You nurture the collective and through friendship. Unconventional care. May seem detached personally.
in_signs.Pisces: You nurture through empathy and spiritual connection. Boundaryless compassion. Can lose self in care-giving.

2.name: Pallas
2.keywords: wisdom, strategy, creative intelligence, pattern recognition, healing
2.interpretation: Pallas (Pallas Athena) shows your wisdom, how you solve problems creatively, your strategic thinking, and capacity for pattern recognition. This is the warrior-artist asteroid - combining intellect with action, wisdom with craft.

in_signs.Aries: Quick strategic thinking. Warrior wisdom. You solve problems through direct action and bold moves.
in_signs.Taurus: Patient strategic planning. Wisdom through the senses. You solve problems through practical, grounded approaches.
in_signs.Gemini: Intellectual strategy. Multiple solution thinking. You solve problems through communication and clever tactics.
in_signs.Cancer: Emotional intelligence. Intuitive strategy. You solve problems by reading feelings and protective instincts.
in_signs.Leo: Creative problem-solving. Dramatic wisdom. You solve problems through self-expression and confident action.
in_signs.Virgo: Analytical strategy. Precise wisdom. You solve problems through detailed analysis and systematic approaches.
in_signs.Libra: Diplomatic strategy. Wisdom through balance. You solve problems through negotiation and aesthetic solutions.
in_signs.Scorpio: Psychological strategy. Deep wisdom. You solve problems by understanding hidden motivations and power dynamics.
in_signs.Sagittarius: Philosophical strategy. Expansive wisdom. You solve problems through seeing the bigger picture and taking risks.
in_signs.Capricorn: Executive strategy. Mature wisdom. You solve problems through structure, authority, and long-term planning.
in_signs.Aquarius: Innovative strategy. Revolutionary wisdom. You solve problems through unconventional, future-oriented thinking.
in_signs.Pisces: Intuitive strategy. Mystical wisdom. You solve problems through spiritual insight and artistic vision.

3.name: Juno
3.keywords: marriage, partnership, commitment, jealousy, equality in relationship
3.interpretation: Juno shows what you need in committed partnership, your marriage style, issues of loyalty and jealousy, and the quality you seek in a life partner. This is the wife asteroid - your relationship with commitment itself.

in_signs.Aries: You need independence within commitment. Partner must respect your autonomy. Can be competitive in relationships.
in_signs.Taurus: You need stability and sensuality in commitment. Loyal but possessive. Material security matters in partnership.
in_signs.Gemini: You need intellectual connection and variety in commitment. Mental stimulation keeps partnership alive. Can be inconsistent.
in_signs.Cancer: You need emotional security and nurturing in commitment. Family-oriented partnerships. Can be moody or clingy.
in_signs.Leo: You need admiration and romance in commitment. Generous but expect loyalty. Partnership must be special and celebrated.
in_signs.Virgo: You need practicality and service in commitment. Helpful but critical. Partnership must be useful and improving.
in_signs.Libra: You need equality and harmony in commitment. Natural at partnership but can lose self. Marriage is central to identity.
in_signs.Scorpio: You need depth and intensity in commitment. Passionate but jealous. Partnership must transform and merge souls.
in_signs.Sagittarius: You need freedom and growth in commitment. Adventurous but reluctant to be tied down. Partnership must expand horizons.
in_signs.Capricorn: You need respect and stability in commitment. Traditional values. Partnership must support ambitions.
in_signs.Aquarius: You need friendship and independence in commitment. Unconventional partnerships. Need space within togetherness.
in_signs.Pisces: You need spiritual and romantic unity in commitment. Idealistic about partnership. Can be self-sacrificing or disappointed.

4.name: Vesta
4.keywords: sacred service, devotion, focus, sexuality, what you tend
4.interpretation: Vesta shows where you focus devotedly, your sacred service, relationship with sexuality and commitment to cause. This is the priestess asteroid - what you tend like a sacred flame, and where you can be celibate in service to something greater.

in_signs.Aries: Devoted to independence and initiative. Sacred fire of self. Sexuality tied to conquest and freedom.
in_signs.Taurus: Devoted to stability and beauty. Sacred relationship with body. Sexuality tied to sensuality and loyalty.
in_signs.Gemini: Devoted to learning and communication. Sacred mind. Sexuality tied to mental connection and variety.
in_signs.Cancer: Devoted to family and emotional security. Sacred home. Sexuality tied to emotional safety and nurturing.
in_signs.Leo: Devoted to creativity and self-expression. Sacred self. Sexuality tied to being adored and dramatic passion.
in_signs.Virgo: Devoted to service and perfection. Sacred work. Sexuality tied to purity and health consciousness.
in_signs.Libra: Devoted to harmony and partnership. Sacred relationship. Sexuality tied to beauty and equality.
in_signs.Scorpio: Devoted to transformation and depth. Sacred intensity. Sexuality is transformative, powerful, possibly celibate or extreme.
in_signs.Sagittarius: Devoted to truth and freedom. Sacred quest. Sexuality tied to adventure and philosophical connection.
in_signs.Capricorn: Devoted to achievement and responsibility. Sacred ambition. Sexuality controlled, tied to respect and status.
in_signs.Aquarius: Devoted to innovation and humanity. Sacred ideals. Sexuality unconventional, possibly detached or collective-focused.
in_signs.Pisces: Devoted to spirituality and transcendence. Sacred compassion. Sexuality mystical, possibly celibate or merged with divine.

433.name: Eros
433.keywords: erotic love, passion, desire, what turns you on
433.interpretation: Eros shows your erotic nature, what you find sexually attractive, how you experience desire, and the nature of your turn-ons. This is passion itself - raw, sexual, magnetic attraction.

in_signs.Aries: Turned on by confidence, aggression, competition. Direct sexual expression. Quick arousal and conquest.
in_signs.Taurus: Turned on by sensuality, touch, luxury. Slow, physical seduction. Enduring passion through the senses.
in_signs.Gemini: Turned on by wit, conversation, variety. Mental seduction. Curiosity and experimentation in intimacy.
in_signs.Cancer: Turned on by emotion, nurturing, familiarity. Need safety for passion. Desire tied to feelings and care.
in_signs.Leo: Turned on by attention, drama, being desired. Passionate display. Generous and theatrical in intimacy.
in_signs.Virgo: Turned on by service, health, perfection. Modest but particular. Passion through attention to detail.
in_signs.Libra: Turned on by beauty, romance, equality. Aesthetic seduction. Desire for balanced, harmonious intimacy.
in_signs.Scorpio: Turned on by intensity, power, taboo. Transformative sexuality. Deep, possessive, all-consuming desire.
in_signs.Sagittarius: Turned on by adventure, freedom, philosophy. Exploratory passion. Desire for meaning and expansion.
in_signs.Capricorn: Turned on by authority, achievement, maturity. Controlled passion. Desire for respect and mastery.
in_signs.Aquarius: Turned on by uniqueness, friendship, innovation. Unconventional sexuality. Desire for mental and social connection.
in_signs.Pisces: Turned on by spirituality, fantasy, merging. Romantic idealism. Desire for transcendent, boundaryless union.

16.name: Psyche
16.keywords: soul connection, psychological depth, the beloved, trials in love
16.interpretation: Psyche shows your soul's journey in love, psychological needs in relationship, and the trials you undergo to achieve true intimacy. This is the soul-mate asteroid - where you meet your deepest self through another.

in_signs.Aries: Soul grows through independence battles. Psychological need to be first. Trials involving courage and self-assertion.
in_signs.Taurus: Soul grows through material and sensory experience. Psychological need for stability. Trials involving worth and attachment.
in_signs.Gemini: Soul grows through communication and learning. Psychological need for mental connection. Trials involving truth and commitment.
in_signs.Cancer: Soul grows through emotional bonding and family. Psychological need for safety. Trials involving vulnerability and boundaries.
in_signs.Leo: Soul grows through self-expression and being seen. Psychological need for recognition. Trials involving pride and authenticity.
in_signs.Virgo: Soul grows through service and refinement. Psychological need for usefulness. Trials involving perfectionism and acceptance.
in_signs.Libra: Soul grows through relationship and balance. Psychological need for partnership. Trials involving self-loss and equality.
in_signs.Scorpio: Soul grows through transformation and depth. Psychological need for intensity. Trials involving trust and power.
in_signs.Sagittarius: Soul grows through exploration and meaning. Psychological need for freedom. Trials involving commitment and truth.
in_signs.Capricorn: Soul grows through achievement and responsibility. Psychological need for respect. Trials involving vulnerability and time.
in_signs.Aquarius: Soul grows through innovation and detachment. Psychological need for independence. Trials involving connection and humanity.
in_signs.Pisces: Soul grows through compassion and transcendence. Psychological need for union. Trials involving boundaries and reality.

hypothetical_bodies.description: These are hypothetical or esoteric points used in Uranian and alternative astrology. They are for exploratory and entertainment purposes rather than traditional interpretation.

Cupido.keywords: unions, artistry, group bonds, aesthetic connection
Cupido.interpretation: Cupido is linked with togetherness, social magnetism, and the urge to create or belong to a tribe. It highlights where you seek beauty, harmony and shared creative or relational experiences.

Hades.keywords: decay, the underbelly, shadow work, old karma
Hades.interpretation: Hades points to what is hidden, decaying, or uncomfortable but necessary to face. It can describe taboo material, old karma, and the need to compost the past into wisdom.

Zeus.keywords: focused will, ignition, directed energy, ambition
Zeus.interpretation: Zeus concentrates drive and willpower. It shows where you can harness firepower, turn raw desire into a targeted plan, and initiate projects with force and precision.

Kronos.interpretation: Kronos is about elevated status and the urge to rise above the ordinary. It can show where you seek mastery, command respect, and feel called to operate from a higher standard.

Apollon.interpretation: Apollon spreads things out. It relates to broad networks, commerce, education, scientific thinking and the ability to handle many threads at once without losing the bigger picture.

Admetos.interpretation: Admetos slows and concentrates. It can indicate where life feels stuck or heavy, but also where deep mastery, endurance and intense focus are possible over time.

Vulcanus.keywords: raw power, pressure, forging, inner strength
Vulcanus.interpretation: Vulcanus symbolizes compressed power and the forging fire. It highlights where you can develop immense inner strength, or where pressure builds until transformation becomes unavoidable.

Poseidon.interpretation: Poseidon is linked with spiritual clarity, inspiration and subtle perception. It marks where your intuition, ideals and quest for meaning are especially active.

Isis-Transpluto.interpretation: Isis-Transpluto points to an exacting, refining influence. It can describe where you strive for purity, self-sufficiency and razor-sharp discernment, sometimes to the point of over-critique.

Nibiru.keywords: collective disruption, long cycles, awakening shocks
Nibiru.interpretation: Nibiru is used as a symbol for large-scale shifts and disruptive cycles. It can indicate where you experience periodic upheavals that crack open awareness and reset the landscape.

Vulcan.keywords: inner forge, invisible work, sub-solar will
Vulcan.interpretation: Vulcan, the hypothetical intramercurian body, symbolizes invisible forging close to the heart of your identity. It highlights subtle inner work that shapes will, temperament and resilience.

Selena.keywords: idealized purity, inner light, protective grace
Selena.interpretation: Selena or White Moon represents an inner ideal of purity and quiet protection. It can show where you feel guided, blessed or held to a gentler, more luminous standard.

Proserpina.interpretation: Proserpina speaks to crossing thresholds and reclaiming power after a descent. It marks where you move between worlds, identities or roles and slowly stabilize a new form.

Waldemath.keywords: ghost echoes, emotional residue, unseen tides
Waldemath.interpretation: Waldemath’s ‘Dark Moon’ is associated with ghost-like emotional patterns and subtle psychic weather. It can show where invisible tides and past echoes quietly tug at your feelings.

Planet_9.keywords: deep background fate, outer patterning, remote influence
Planet_9.interpretation: Planet 9 symbolizes remote but powerful background influences. It can describe slow-moving themes, ancestral patterns or collective currents that shape your life from far out of conscious view.

Christ_Comet.keywords: crisis of meaning, epochal turning points, revelation
Christ_Comet.interpretation: The Christ Comet is used symbolically for turning points that reframe meaning. It may highlight where crises or rare events catalyze a change in worldview or spiritual orientation.
